<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>POWER STEERING GEAR: TRW/ROSS-TAS 40, 55, 65 AND 85 - ASSEMBLE - HOUSING PORTS, PLUGS, SCREWS, FITTINGS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0500318" svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>HOUSING PORTS, PLUGS, SCREWS, FITTINGS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If damaged, remove and replace the poppet fixed stop screw and washer if equipped. Replace
                with poppet fixed stop screw and discard the washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f05003d3">Figure 133</hotlnk>). Tighten to 48 ft-lbs. (65 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
            <figure id="f05003d3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g05003d3" filename="../figg05/G05003D3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 133. Replace Poppet Fixed Stop Screw</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If damaged, remove poppet adjusting screw and sealing nut without allowing the nut to change
                its position on the screw (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f05003d4">Figure 134</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f05003d4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g05003d4" filename="../figg05/G05003D4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 134. Remove Poppet Adjusting Screw</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Assemble the new nut onto the new adjusting screw, matching its position to the nut and screw removed
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f05003d4">Figure 134</hotlnk>). Tighten sealing nut to 35 ft-lbs. (47 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If damaged, remove and replace automatic bleed plug (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f05003d5">Figure 135</hotlnk>). Tighten to 48 ft-lbs. (65 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
            <figure id="f05003d5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g05003d5" filename="../figg05/G05003D5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 135. Remove Automatic Bleed Plug</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>If damaged, remove and replace permanent auxiliary port plugs and O-rings. Assemble new O-rings on
                port plugs and tighten to 30 ft-lbs. (41 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If damaged, remove and replace manual bleed screw (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f05003d6">Figure 136</hotlnk>). Tighten to 30 in-lbs. (3.4 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
            <figure id="f05003d6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g05003d6" filename="../figg05/G05003D6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="192px"
                         scalefitheight="152px"/>
                <caption>Figure 136. Remove Manual Bleed Screw</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
